{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8b9ee4f0aeb1d838", "type": "tool_result", "content": "=== search paper 2603.13686 ===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2603.13686\", \"title\": \"$\\u03c4$-Voice: Benchmarking Full-Duplex Voice Agents on Real-World Domains\", \"authors\": [\"Soham Ray\", \"Keshav Dhandhania\", \"Victor Barres\", \"Karthik Narasimhan\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.AI\"], \"topic\": \"speech_agent\", \"tags\": [\"Eval\", \"Eval/\\u57fa\\u51c6\", \"Eval/\\u60c5\\u611f\\u8bed\\u5883\\u4ea4\\u4e92\", \"Eval/\\u5b89\\u5168\\u6027\", \"Agent\", \"Agent/\\u5bf9\\u8bdd\\u578bLALM\"], \"contributions\": [\"A voice agent benchmark combining verifiable completion of complex grounded tasks, full-duplex interaction, and realistic audio.\", \"A controllable and realistic voice user simulator with diverse accents, realistic audio environments, and rich turn-taking dynamics.\", \"Empirical findings revealing a substantial voice-text gap where voice agents retain only 30-45% of text capability under realistic conditions.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"\\u03c4\\u00b2-bench\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Uses \\u03c4\\u00b2-bench's 3 domains with 278 tasks for evaluation and follows its method for task completion assessment\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"gpt-realtime-1.5\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"OpenAI's audio-native model evaluated and compared as a speech agent baseline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"gemini-live-2.5-flash-native-audio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Google's audio-native model evaluated and compared as a speech agent baseline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"grok-voice-agent\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"xAI's audio-native model evaluated and compared as a speech agent baseline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-4.1\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used as the user simulator LLM and as a non-reasoning text baseline for comparison\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"ElevenLabs v3\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used as the TTS engine for the user simulator at 24kHz\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-5\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Mentioned as the text SOTA baseline achieving 85% pass@1\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"G.711\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u03bc-law compression standard applied to simulate real telephone line conditions\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gilbert-Elliott model\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to simulate packet loss and frame drops in the acoustic environment\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Full-duplex voice agents--systems that listen and speak simultaneously--are rapidly moving from research to production. However, existing evaluations address conversational dynamics and task completion in isolation. We introduce $\\u03c4$-voice, a benchmark for evaluating voice agents on grounded tasks with real-world complexity: agents must navigate complex multi-turn conversations, adhere to domain policies, and interact with the environment. The framework extends $\\u03c4^2$-bench into a novel voice agent benchmark combining verifiable completion of complex grounded tasks, full-duplex interaction, and realistic audio--enabling direct comparison between voice and text performance. A controllable and realistic voice user simulator provides diverse accents, realistic audio environments, and rich turn-taking dynamics; by decoupling simulation from wall-clock time, the user simulator can use the most capable LLM without real-time constraints. We evaluate task completion (pass@1) and voice interaction quality across 278 tasks: while GPT-5 (reasoning) achieves 85%, voice agents reach only 31--51% under clean conditions and 26--38% under realistic conditions with noise and diverse accents--retaining only 30--45% of text capability; qualitative analysis confirms 79--90% of failures stem from agent behavior, suggesting that observed failures primarily reflect agent behavior under our evaluation setup. $\\u03c4$-voice provides a reproducible testbed for measuring progress toward voice agents that are natural, conversational, and reliable.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-28T04:59:34.924432\"}\n=== search paper 2603.08216 ===\nPaper 2603.08216 not found\n=== search paper 2410.00037 ===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2410.00037\", \"title\": \"Moshi: a speech-text foundation model for real-time dialogue\", \"authors\": [\"Alexandre D\\u00e9fossez\", \"Laurent Mazar\\u00e9\", \"Manu Orsini\", \"Am\\u00e9lie Royer\", \"Patrick P\\u00e9rez\", \"Herv\\u00e9 J\\u00e9gou\", \"Edouard Grave\", \"Neil Zeghidour\"], \"year\": 2024, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"eess.AS\", \"cs.AI\", \"cs.CL\", \"cs.LG\", \"cs.SD\"], \"topic\": \"dialogue_system\", \"tags\": [\"LALM\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29\", \"TTS\", \"LALM/\\u5bf9\\u8bdd\\u578b\", \"LALM/\\u97f3\\u9891\\u6807\\u8bb0-\\u878d\\u5408\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u91cf\\u5316-RVQ\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u8bed\\u4e49\\u58f0\\u5b66-\\u6df7\\u5408\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u6d41\\u5f0f\"], \"contributions\": [\"We present Helium, a 7B-parameter text LLM pre-trained on 2.1T tokens of filtered public English data.\", \"We train Mimi, a neural audio codec that distills semantic information into the first level of acoustic tokens using a split residual vector quantizer.\", \"We propose a new hierarchical, streaming architecture for audio language modeling that extends the RQ-Transformer with per-codebook parameters and acoustic delays to jointly generate semantic and acoustic tokens.\", \"We introduce a multi-stream audio language model architecture that explicitly processes the input and output audio streams in parallel to handle full-duplex dialogues with arbitrary conversational dynamics.\", \"We introduce Inner Monologue, a training and inference method that predicts time-aligned text tokens as a prefix to audio tokens to significantly improve the linguistic quality of generated speech while remaining compatible with streaming inference.\", \"We demonstrate that adjusting the delay between text and audio tokens within the Inner Monologue framework allows a single model to function as both a streaming ASR and a streaming TTS system.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2306.09633\", \"title\": \"MPT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Text baseline compared against Helium in text benchmarks.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2306.01116\", \"title\": \"Falcon\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Text baseline compared against Helium in text benchmarks.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2307.09288\", \"title\": \"Llama 2\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Text baseline compared against Helium in text benchmarks.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2402.00838\", \"title\": \"OLMo\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Text baseline compared against Helium in text benchmarks.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2310.06825\", \"title\": \"Mistral\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Text baseline compared against Helium in text benchmarks.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2403.08295\", \"title\": \"Gemma 1\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Text baseline compared against Helium in text benchmarks.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2401.02755\", \"title\": \"Whisper\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Used to extract text-audio alignments for Inner Monologue training data preparation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2310.06825\", \"title\": \"Mistral\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Safety baseline compared against Moshi on the ALERT benchmark.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"We introduce Moshi, a speech-text foundation model and full-duplex spoken dialogue framework. Current systems for spoken dialogue rely on pipelines of independent components, namely voice activity detection, speech recognition, textual dialogue and text-to-speech. Such frameworks cannot emulate the experience of real conversations. First, their complexity induces a latency of several seconds between interactions. Second, text being the intermediate modality for dialogue, non-linguistic information that modifies meaning -- such as emotion or non-speech sounds -- is lost in the interaction. Finally, they rely on a segmentation into speaker turns, which does not take into account overlapping speech, interruptions and interjections. Moshi solves these independent issues altogether by casting spoken dialogue as speech-to-speech generation. Starting from a text language model backbone, Moshi generates speech as tokens from the residual quantizer of a neural audio codec, while modeling separately its own speech and that of the user into parallel streams. This allows for the removal of explicit speaker turns, and the modeling of arbitrary conversational dynamics. We moreover extend the hierarchical semantic-to-acoustic token generation of previous work to first predict time-aligned text tokens as a prefix to audio tokens. Not only this \\\"Inner Monologue\\\" method significantly improves the linguistic quality of generated speech, but we also illustrate how it can provide streaming speech recognition and text-to-speech. Our resulting model is the first real-time full-duplex spoken large language model, with a theoretical latency of 160ms, 200ms in practice, and is available at https://github.com/kyutai-labs/moshi.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T04:20:04.774188\"}", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "b483957f-f443-4a4f-9967-33d535cead71", "uuid": "1d5d9f8d-b99a-473a-96c3-3ca5079a3de0", "timestamp": "2026-07-06T09:55:49.402Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "=== search paper 2603.13686 ===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2603.13686\", \"title\": \"$\\u03c4$-Voice: Benchmarking Full-Duplex Voice Agents on Real-World Domains\", \"authors\": [\"Soham Ray\", \"Keshav Dhandhania\", \"Victor Barres\", \"Karthik Narasimhan\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.AI\"], \"topic\": \"speech_agent\", \"tags\": [\"Eval\", \"Eval/\\u57fa\\u51c6\", \"Eval/\\u60c5\\u611f\\u8bed\\u5883\\u4ea4\\u4e92\", \"Eval/\\u5b89\\u5168\\u6027\", \"Agent\", \"Agent/\\u5bf9\\u8bdd\\u578bLALM\"], \"contributions\": [\"A voice agent benchmark combining verifiable completion of complex grounded tasks, full-duplex interaction, and realistic audio.\", \"A controllable and realistic voice user simulator with diverse accents, realistic audio environments, and rich turn-taking dynamics.\", \"Empirical findings revealing a substantial voice-text gap where voice agents retain only 30-45% of text capability under realistic conditions.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"\\u03c4\\u00b2-bench\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Uses \\u03c4\\u00b2-bench's 3 domains with 278 tasks for evaluation and follows its method for task completion assessment\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"gpt-realtime-1.5\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"cont