{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-81eaa0ac1485a46c", "type": "tool_result", "content": "=== 2606.02400 ===\nTITLE: SoulX-Transcriber: A Robust End-to-End Framework for Multi-Speaker Speech Transcription\nCONTRIB: []\nABSTRACT: Recent advances in Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) and Large Language Models (LLMs) have significantly improved speech understanding capabilities. However, multi-speaker speech transcription remains challenging task, constrained by highly similar speaker voices, rapid turn-taking transitions, overlapping utterances and inaccurate speaker boundary segmentation. These challenges become particularly pronounced in real-world conversational audio, where speaker dynamics and acoustic conditions are highly variable. This technical report presents SoulX-Transcriber, a unified multi-speaker transcri\n=== concept naturalness metric ===\n=== concept response timing ===\n=== concept perturbation benchmark ===\n2509.09550\n2509.21749\n2604.22225\n2512.19090\n2509.22220\n2606.06357\n2606.11722\n2605.07915\n2512.04552\n2508.10711\n=== concept NLL scoring ===\n=== concept judge model ===\n2606.03116\n2605.23261\n=== method causal prediction ===\n=== concept overlap speech ===", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "b483957f-f443-4a4f-9967-33d535cead71", "uuid": "70ffd0c9-fd95-428c-8514-92c79f19a858", "timestamp": "2026-07-06T09:57:28.407Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "=== 2606.02400 ===\nTITLE: SoulX-Transcriber: A Robust End-to-End Framework for Multi-Speaker Speech Transcription\nCONTRIB: []\nABSTRACT: Recent advances in Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) and Large Language Models (LLMs) have significantly improved speech understanding capabilities. However, multi-speaker speech transcription remains challenging task, constrained by highly similar speaker voices, rapid turn-taking transitions, overlapping utterances and inaccurate speaker boundary segmentation. These challenges become particularly pronounced in real-world conversational audio, where speaker dynamics and acoustic conditions are highly variable. This technical report presents SoulX-Transcriber, a unified multi-speaker transcri\n=== concept naturalness metric ===\n=== concept response timing ===\n=== concept perturbation benchmark ===\n2509.09550\n2509.21749\n2604.22225\n2512.19090\n2509.22220\n2606.06357\n2606.11722\n2605.07915\n2512.04552\n2508.10711\n=== concept NLL scoring ===\n=== concept judge model ===\n2606.03116\n2605.23261\n=== method causal prediction ===\n=== concept overlap speech ===", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
